  "title": "Audit Assistant or Audit Associate",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li><p>To perform statutory audit for different type of entities (e.g. Companies, branches, MCST etc.) in accordance to Singapore Financial Reporting Standards (“SFRS”) and Singapore Standards on Auditing (“SSA”).</p></li><li><p>To prepare audited financial statements in accordance with SFRS and SSA.</p></li><li><p>To prepare full tax computations and relevant schedules.</p></li><li><p>Handle accounting assignments and other ad-hoc projects as assigned.</p></li><li><p>Follow up on client and engagement outstanding matters independently.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Possess a minimum of Bachelor's degree in Accountancy, ACCA, CPA or other relevant bachelor's degrees will be considered.</p></li><li><p>Candidate who started Singapore CA Qualification (f.k.a SQP Programmes) under SAC will be preferred.</p></li><li><p>Candidate who has completed all ACCA modules will be preferred.</p></li><li><p>Preferably experience in Finance – Audit / Taxation or equivalent.</p></li><li><p>Minimum 1 to 2 years of experience in auditing practice.</p></li></ul><p><br /><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Initiative and have the drive to learn.</p></li><li><p>Positive working attitude.</p></li><li><p>Posses initiative and able to work independently.</p></li><li><p>Able to work under stress and work overtime during peak period.</p></li><li><p>Candidates must have a good written and verbal communication skills and sound IT competences.</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with Microsoft Word and Excel.</p></li><li><p>Required language (s) : Mandarin (to liaise with Mandarin speaking clients) & English.</p></li></ul><p><br />\n\nOnly shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p><br /></p><p>Please send your updated resume to <strong>hr@prestigepac.com</strong> if you are interested.</p><p><br /></p><p>Note:  We do not have work permit quotas available for applicants from Myanmar and Vietnam at this moment. </p>",
